## THIS SESSION'S WORK (12 priorities, batch pre-APPROVED user-path)

**P1 — Free-spark soft-cap @ 50**
- `src/constants.ts` (+5) — `FREE_SPARK_SOFT_CAP = 50`
- `src/state/world.ts` (+13) — `DESPAWN_SPARK` action; refuses to despawn
  Carried sparks; silent no-op on missing id
- `src/main.ts` (+25) — `enforceFreeSparkCap()` runs after spawn each tick;
  oldest by `createdTick` despawns first via dispatch seam (§ 10.2)

**P2 — Structure-immobility runtime guard (DEV-only)**
- `src/game/invariants.ts` (NEW, 124 LOC) — `snapshotInvariants()`,
  `verifyInvariants()`, `snapPrevPosForUnbonded()`. Catches:
  - immobility (unbonded primitive moved tick-over-tick — bug in caller)
  - non-finite primitive/spark positions (NaN/Infinity from solver blow-up)
  - color-inheritance break (Phase 1 placerColor === ownerColor)
- `src/main.ts` (+14) — pre-tick snapshot, post-tick verify, throttled
  console.error every 60 ticks if a violation persists
- All gated by `import.meta.env.DEV` — zero prod cost

**P3 — Effects layer + bond-commit pop + sever-erase fade**
- `src/game/effects.ts` (NEW, 30 LOC) — `GameEffect` discriminated union
  (`BOND_COMMIT` | `SEVER_ERASE`), `EFFECT_LIFETIME_TICKS=36`
- `src/state/world.ts` (+8) — `world.effects[]` queue field; `dispatch` pushes
  events on PLACE_PRIMITIVE (BOND_COMMIT) and SEVER_BOND (SEVER_ERASE per
  loser); save.ts ignores it (effects not persisted)
- `src/render/effectsRenderer.ts` (NEW, 110 LOC) — drains queue, ages with
  world.tick (NOT wall-clock — pauses with simulation), renders expanding
  ring + flash for commit, ghost shrink + shockwave for erase

**P4 — Energy-gauge ease + win-banner fade**
- `src/render/ui.ts` (rewrite of `drawEnergyGauge`/`drawProgress`/`drawWinState`)
  — 12% per-frame lerp toward target; bar glides instead of stepping;
  glow accent at fill edge; win banner fades in/out via alpha lerp

**P5 — Stiffness-tier preview color on connect-drag**
- `src/render/structureRenderer.ts` (+25) — `lookupCombo()` in preview path;
  TIER_COLOR map (LOW=amber, MID=yellow, HIGH=mint); 3-bar glyph next to
  cursor showing locked-in tier; line width scales with tier

**P6 — Bond strain visualization (red-shift near break)**
- `src/render/structureRenderer.ts` (+20) — per-bond strain ratio; lerps
  base tint toward 0xff3030 by `stress*0.85`; pulse overlay when stress
  > 0.7 (animated alpha rises with stress); width grows above mid-stress

**P7 — Stats overlay expansion**
- `src/render/statsOverlay.ts` (+50) — new `recordWorld(world, effectsCount)`
  hook; adds rows: free/cap, prims, bonds, worst strain, fx count; turns
  red when free@cap or worst-strain > 0.7

**P8 — Keyboard 'R' reset in POSTGAME**
- `src/main.ts` (+7) — `resetIfPostgame()` extracted; window keydown 'R'/'r'
  triggers it when gameState === POSTGAME; canvas-click still works

**P9 — Stress harness (60s default, 10-min via STRESS_FULL=1)**
- `src/physics/stress.test.ts` (NEW, 138 LOC) — builds 30-prim chain via
  dispatch, runs Spawner + 8-substep physics + invariant verify each tick
  for 3600 ticks (60s) or 36000 ticks (10min). Asserts: no NaN, no
  immobility violations, free-spark count never > cap+1, worst tick < 50ms

**P10 — New tests**
- `src/game/session5.test.ts` (NEW, 226 LOC, 15 tests):
  - 4 soft-cap tests (despawn, refuse Carried, missing-id, oldest-by-tick)
  - 6 invariant tests (immobility flag, bonded-allowed, NaN prim+spark,
    color, snap helper)
  - 3 effects tests (BOND_COMMIT emission, SEVER_ERASE per loser, save.ts
    excludes effects field)
  - 2 strain auto-sever tests (solveBonds reports break, dispatch removes)

**P11 — Bond strain auto-sever (FIX of latent S2 bug)**
- `solveBonds()` returned broken bond IDs but `main.ts` discarded them —
  strain-break never fired. Fixed in `src/main.ts` substep loop: dispatch
  SEVER_BOND for each broken bond, refresh local bondArr after dispatch,
  next substep continues with new array

**P12 — prevPos snap for orphaned primitives**
- `src/state/world.ts` (+1) — `snapPrevPosForUnbonded(world.primitives)` at
  end of SEVER_BOND handler. Required by P2 immobility guard: when a
  primitive loses its last bond, its prevPos was last set by solver — would
  trip the immobility check on the following tick. The snap resyncs
  prevPos = pos so the guard sees no spurious drift

## OPEN ISSUES
- **Effects active list isn't hard-capped** (only by lifetime). Worst-case
  ~10K entries during mass-sever. Acceptable Phase 1; revisit if a real
  playtest produces a huge cascade
- **Strain auto-sever is now active under normal play.** If user finds
  bonds breaking unexpectedly during natural construction, raise
  `STRAIN_BREAK_BY_TIER` (LOCKED constant — would need amendment) or
  reduce ATTRACT_STRENGTH in controls.ts
- **Headless Claude Preview tab runs ~1/3 speed.** Real-browser playtest
  remains the only way to confirm 60 FPS. Tests cover correctness;
  preview covers smoke-only
- **Color inheritance guard is Phase-1 only** — Phase 2 Steal disruption
  will mutate ownerColor. Will need a softening/disabling pass when Steal
  ships
- **Single-RMB sever vs spec's double-RMB** — choice from Session 2
  preserved this session

