## REFLEXION ENTRIES (this session)
- S5 #strain-break-bug: solveBonds returned broken bond IDs since S1 but
  `main.ts` discarded them — strain-break was dead code. Fixed by
  dispatching SEVER_BOND in the substep loop. Lesson: when a function
  returns a non-trivial value, audit every call site to verify it's
  consumed. The bond-solver's "broken" return existed in API but was
  never wired — classic latent bug
- S5 #immobility-snap: bonded → unbonded transition leaves prevPos stale
  (solver only mutates pos). Without `snapPrevPosForUnbonded()`, the
  immobility guard would (correctly!) flag residual drift on the
  following tick. Required pairing with the guard, not optional
- S5 #effects-via-queue: chose `world.effects: GameEffect[]` over an
  external EventBus or callback in dispatch signature. Keeps the
  dispatch seam intact (Phase 3 networking still drops in unchanged) and
  save.ts trivially ignores the field via explicit-enumeration of
  serialized properties. Pattern to repeat for any future side-channel
- S5 #headless-rAF: Claude Preview headless tab runs Pixi ticker at
  ~1/3 wall-clock speed. State queries are reliable; visual sync is
  delayed. Pre-existing S1 reflexion confirmed; this session's playtest
  uses programmatic dispatch + sleep-then-readback, not real-time
  interaction
- S5 #stress-test-tradeoff: full 10-minute run is gated by
  STRESS_FULL=1 env var (process.env-style check via globalThis sniff to
  avoid @types/node). Default 60s in CI keeps the suite under 5s while
  the mechanism is provable on demand
- SESSION #anti-bloat: largest module unchanged at 278 LOC (controls.ts).
  effectsRenderer.ts came in at 110, invariants.ts at 124. Charter
  comfortably held
- SESSION #council-skipped: user "Session priority batch pre-APPROVED!"
  satisfied Rule 17 user-path. PRIME-AUDIT pass at end caught:
  effects-list-no-hard-cap (acknowledged), strain-now-aggressive
  (logged), spec-untouched (verified). All findings folded into open
  issues / next steps

